719200f-b.title: Manhattan: Convent Avenue - 151st Street (West)
719200f-b.text:
(1)
479 Convent Ave., at the S.E. corner of West 151st Street. Also
shown is West 151st Street, south side, east from and including Convent,
to, but not including St. Nicholas Ave. The 2 buildings Nos. 479
Convent Ave., and 416 West 151st Street are frame structures.
September 1, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
(2) The same; a rear view, from Convent Ave.
September 1, 1935.
P. L. Spear.

719199f-a.title: Manhattan: Convent Avenue - 151st Street
719199f-a.text:
179 Convent Avenue, a three-story fraue residence at the S.E. corner
of 15lst Street. Also shown is 416 West 151st Street, a two-story
frame house at the S.E. corner of Amsterdam Avenue.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 492.
